http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/title.value: Arizona Standards for the Visual Arts

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: We recognize that quality learning in the visual arts can take many forms and be exemplified by exposure to a range of media, processes, and artists throughout time. The Arizona Standards for the Visual Arts create a broad structure within which highly qualified art teachers, with the support of the school district or charter administration, will design a rich, articulated curriculum that meets all standards at the developmental level represented by the schools' population. Each curriculum will provide an opportunity for students to fulfill Beginning, Intermediate, and Advanced performance objectives by the twelfth grade.
Create

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Student will create artworks to communicate ideas, meanings, and/or purposes.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Creative Process

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: The student will develop, revise, and reflect on ideas for expression in his or her own artwork.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Beginning
Contribute to a discussion about ideas for his or her own artwork .
Contribute to a discussion about ideas for his or her own artwork .
Make and explain revisions in his or her own artwork .
Intermediate
Contribute to a discussion about ideas for his or her own artwork .
Make and explain revisions in his or her own artwork .
Develop plans for his or her own artwork , (e.g., sketches, models, and notes).
Advanced

Distinction
Develop and revise plans, (e.g., sketches, models, and notes) for his or her own artwork and select the best option.
